Create react app
npx create-react-app my-app # to create project name  my-app
cd my-app #change directory(folder)
npm start # to start react application 

public/index.html: it sereves as the enrty point for app
scr/index.js: react app where the DOM is rendered
scr/APP.JS: serves as root of component tree
scr/components: a folder to store resuasble components
1)components (core building blocks of a react appliactions)
--they help to create reusable block of code
--if any thing goes wrong in 


App.js
import React from 'react';
import './App.css';
import Welcome1 from './components/welcome1';
function App() {
  return (
 
    <div>
      <Welcome1 name ="thirmal" greeting="hello"></Welcome1>
      <Welcome1 name ="raj" greeting="hii"></Welcome1>
    </div>
    
  );
};
export default App;

Welcome.js
import React from 'react';
const Welcome1=(props)=>{
    const{name, greeting}=props;

    return(
        <h1 className="message">{greeting},{name}</h1>
    )
}
export default Welcome1;

